\subsection*{Esercizio 1: Vocabulary - Collocations}
Complete the sentences with the most appropriate word to form a correct collocation.
\begin{enumerate}[a)]
    \item She always felt a great sense of \underline{} when she visited her grandparents. (belonging / possession / ownership) (1 pt)
    \item The company decided to \underline{} its operations to a new location. (relocate / move / transfer) (1 pt)
    \item It's important to \underline{} a healthy lifestyle with regular exercise. (maintain / keep / hold) (1 pt)
    \item The news was so shocking that he \underline{} his words. (swallowed / ate / bit) (1 pt)
    \item After the long hike, they were \underline{} exhausted. (completely / totally / absolutely) (1 pt)
\end{enumerate}

\subsection*{Esercizio 2: Verb Tenses - Present Perfect vs Past Simple}
Choose the correct verb tense to complete each sentence.
\begin{enumerate}[a)]
    \item I \underline{} (see/saw) that movie last week. (1 pt)
    \item She \underline{} (live/has lived) in London for five years. (1 pt)
    \item They \underline{} (not finish/haven't finished) their project yet. (1 pt)
    \item When \underline{} you \underline{} (did you buy/have you bought) that car? (1 pt)
    \item He \underline{} (visit/has visited) Paris twice in his life. (1 pt)
\end{enumerate}

\subsection*{Esercizio 3: Articles - Definite, Indefinite, Zero}
Fill in the blanks with a/an, the, or leave the space blank (Ø) if no article is needed.
\begin{enumerate}[a)]
    \item She is \underline{} excellent doctor. (1 pt)
    \item \underline{} sun is very bright today. (1 pt)
    \item I usually have \underline{} breakfast at 7 AM. (1 pt)
    \item \underline{} Eiffel Tower is in Paris. (1 pt)
    \item They are going on \underline{} holiday next month. (1 pt)
\end{enumerate}

\subsection*{Esercizio 4: Prepositions of Time and Place}
Complete the sentences with the correct prepositions (in, on, at, for, since).
\begin{enumerate}[a)]
    \item The meeting is \underline{} Monday. (1 pt)
    \item He was born \underline{} 1990. (1 pt)
    \item She has been waiting \underline{} two hours. (1 pt)
    \item They live \underline{} London. (1 pt)
    \item I'll see you \underline{} 5 PM. (1 pt)
\end{enumerate}

\subsection*{Esercizio 5: Conditionals - Type 1 and Type 2}
Choose the correct form of the verb to complete the conditional sentences.
\begin{enumerate}[a)]
    \item If it \underline{} (rain/rains) tomorrow, we will stay inside. (1 pt)
    \item If I \underline{} (have/had) more time, I would learn to play the guitar. (1 pt)
    \item She will call you if she \underline{} (needs/need) help. (1 pt)
    \item If they \underline{} (win/won) the lottery, they would buy a new house. (1 pt)
    \item If you study hard, you \underline{} (will pass/would pass) the exam. (1 pt)
\end{enumerate}

